    "client_msg_id": "b4e7a4e1-ae10-46c2-ae57-105425698c1c",
    "text": "As an example of how I've been using model composition in calculang, I added notes to <http://ActuarialPlayground.com|ActuarialPlayground.com> on manipulating the formulas to do mortgage protection - by composing with an old loan calculator model (via just a plain old URL).\nHere are the formula changes, you can interactively swap them on the website, under :speech_balloon:\n<https://github.com/declann/ActuarialPlayground.com/commit/9e487b7e18570e1043ac7f6f4539bf002f8926df#diff-30314a7cf03cb75b7246e76210af5cd0b97071f1ac89a5757d9f62e82a3d1c2d|https://github.com/declann/ActuarialPlayground.com/commit/9e487b7e18570e1043ac7f6f4539bf002f8926df#diff-30314a7cf03cb75b72[…]c89a5757d9f62e82a3d1c2d>",
    "team": "T5TCAFTA9",
    "blocks": [
      {
        "type": "rich_text",
        "block_id": "ceSN9",
        "elements": [
          {
            "type": "rich_text_section",
            "elements": [
              {
                "type": "text",
                "text": "As an example of how I've been using model composition in calculang, I added notes to "
              },
              {
                "type": "link",
                "url": "http://ActuarialPlayground.com",
                "text": "ActuarialPlayground.com"
              },
              {
                "type": "text",
                "text": " on manipulating the formulas to do mortgage protection - by composing with an old loan calculator model (via just a plain old URL).\nHere are the formula changes, you can interactively swap them on the website, under "
